    <refpurpose>Video 4 Linux 2</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
    <literal>input.v4l2</literal> provides access to Video 4 Linux 2 devices.
    </para>

    <refsect3>
    <title>Requirements</title>
    <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>GNU/Linux</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </refsect3>

    <refsect3>
    <title>Input Formats</title>
    <para>None.  This is an input unit.</para>
    </refsect3>

    <refsect3>
    <title>Output Formats</title>
    <para>The exact list of output formats supported by a unit varies with each
    camera.
    </para>

    </refsect3>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
    <title>Controls</title>

    <para>The <literal>input.v4l2</literal> plugin exposes most of the
    controls for a V4L2 device.  The exact number, name, and type of
    each control depends on the device, as different V4L2 devices (and drivers)
    expose different controls.
    </para>

    <para>The full list and description of V4L2 controls can be found in the
    V4L2 API reference.  As of March, 2009, this document is located at
    <ulink url="http://v4l2spec.bytesex.org/spec/">http://v4l2spec.bytesex.org/spec/</ulink>.
    </para>

